          "source_html": "<div class=\"big-section\"><div class=\"group-instruction\"><p><strong>Questions 27 - 31</strong></p><p><br/></p><p>Choose the correct answer.</p></div>\r\n            <div class=\"q-block normal-q\">\r\n                <div class=\"q-stem\">\r\n                    <span class=\"q-num\">27</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"q-text\"><p><strong>What point is the writer making about Robert Cialdini in the first paragraph?</strong></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"opt-list\" style=\"margin:10px 0 10px 25px;\">\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_27\" id=\"opt_27_A\" data-zyz-question=\"q27\" value=\"A\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_27_A\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>A.</strong> He wants to change the way society operates.</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_27\" id=\"opt_27_B\" data-zyz-question=\"q27\" value=\"B\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_27_B\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>B.</strong> He uses a wide variety of research techniques.</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_27\" id=\"opt_27_C\" data-zyz-question=\"q27\" value=\"C\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_27_C\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>C.</strong> He has an unconventional approach to this work.</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_27\" id=\"opt_27_D\" data-zyz-question=\"q27\" value=\"D\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_27_D\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>D.</strong> He refuses to make use of animals in his experiments</label>\r\n        </div></div>\r\n                <button class=\"btn-toggle\">显示解析</button>\r\n                <div class=\"ans-box\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-row\"><strong>正确答案：</strong> C. He has an unconventional approach to this work.</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"analysis\"><p>审题: 题目问的是作者在第一段中关于Robert Cialdini的主要观点是什么。</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>定位关键词: &quot;first paragraph,&quot; &quot;Robert Cialdini&quot;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>对应原文: A段，“Then there is Robert Cialdini, whose unorthodox research involves such mundane items as towels and chocolates. Nonetheless, Cialdini believes he is discovering important insights into how society works, because he is conducting research into why some people are more persuasive than others.”</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>解题思路: A段提到Cialdini采用了一种非传统（<span style=\"text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">unorthodox）</span>的研究方法，通过毛巾和巧克力这些普通的物品等研究为什么有些人比别人更具说服力。</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            </div><div class=\"big-section\">\r\n            <div class=\"q-block normal-q\">\r\n                <div class=\"q-stem\">\r\n                    <span class=\"q-num\">28</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"q-text\"><p><strong>What is the writer doing in the second paragraph?</strong></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"opt-list\" style=\"margin:10px 0 10px 25px;\">\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_28\" id=\"opt_28_A\" data-zyz-question=\"q28\" value=\"A\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_28_A\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>A.</strong> identifying a motivation for the research</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_28\" id=\"opt_28_B\" data-zyz-question=\"q28\" value=\"B\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_28_B\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>B.</strong> assessing on aspect of Cialdini’s character</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_28\" id=\"opt_28_C\" data-zyz-question=\"q28\" value=\"C\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_28_C\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>C.</strong> questioning Cialdini’s scientific research techniques</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_28\" id=\"opt_28_D\" data-zyz-question=\"q28\" value=\"D\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_28_D\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>D.</strong> applauding researchers who examine their own experience</label>\r\n        </div></div>\r\n                <button class=\"btn-toggle\">显示解析</button>\r\n                <div class=\"ans-box\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-row\"><strong>正确答案：</strong> A. identifying a motivation for the research</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"analysis\"><p>审题: 题目问的是作者在第二段中做了什么。</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>定位关键词: &quot;second paragraph&quot;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>对应原文: “Cialdini hopes that, by applying a little science, we should all be able to get our own way more often. ”</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>解题思路: B段提到了Cialdini的研究动机，他希望通过科学研究，所有人都能更频繁地说服其他人。</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            </div><div class=\"big-section\">\r\n            <div class=\"q-block normal-q\">\r\n                <div class=\"q-stem\">\r\n                    <span class=\"q-num\">29</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"q-text\"><p><strong>What are we told about Cialdini’s research methodology?</strong></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"opt-list\" style=\"margin:10px 0 10px 25px;\">\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_29\" id=\"opt_29_A\" data-zyz-question=\"q29\" value=\"A\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_29_A\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>A.</strong> It was conducted in a laboratory.</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_29\" id=\"opt_29_B\" data-zyz-question=\"q29\" value=\"B\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_29_B\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>B.</strong> It involved him taking courses of study.</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_29\" id=\"opt_29_C\" data-zyz-question=\"q29\" value=\"C\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_29_C\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>C.</strong> It was focused on one particular product.</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_29\" id=\"opt_29_D\" data-zyz-question=\"q29\" value=\"D\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_29_D\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>D.</strong> It was based on interviews with salespeople.</label>\r\n        </div></div>\r\n                <button class=\"btn-toggle\">显示解析</button>\r\n                <div class=\"ans-box\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-row\"><strong>正确答案：</strong> B. It involved him taking courses of study.</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"analysis\"><p>审题: 题目问的是Cialdini的研究方法。</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>定位关键词: &quot;Cialdini’s research methodology&quot;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>对应原文: C段，&quot;Having concluded that laboratory experiments on the psychology of persuasion were telling only a part of the story, Cialdini began to probe influence in the real world, enrolling in sales-training programmes.&quot;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>解题思路: <span style=\"text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">C段</span>提到Cialdini通过实际参与销售培训课程来学习如何销售汽车、保险甚至百科全书来学习，这说明他采用了亲身参与学习的方法。</p><p><br/></p><p>同义替换：involved = enrolling</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            </div><div class=\"big-section\">\r\n            <div class=\"q-block normal-q\">\r\n                <div class=\"q-stem\">\r\n                    <span class=\"q-num\">30</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"q-text\"><p><strong>What was Cialdini’s research question for the towel experiment?</strong></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"opt-list\" style=\"margin:10px 0 10px 25px;\">\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_30\" id=\"opt_30_A\" data-zyz-question=\"q30\" value=\"A\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_30_A\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>A.</strong> Is it more effective not to use a card?</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_30\" id=\"opt_30_B\" data-zyz-question=\"q30\" value=\"B\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_30_B\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>B.</strong> Does the message make any difference?</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_30\" id=\"opt_30_C\" data-zyz-question=\"q30\" value=\"C\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_30_C\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>C.</strong> Why is the threat of pollution so persuasive</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_30\" id=\"opt_30_D\" data-zyz-question=\"q30\" value=\"D\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_30_D\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>D.</strong> Can hotels be persuaded to provide more towels?</label>\r\n        </div></div>\r\n                <button class=\"btn-toggle\">显示解析</button>\r\n                <div class=\"ans-box\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-row\"><strong>正确答案：</strong> B. Does the message make any difference?</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"analysis\"><p>审题: 题目问的是Cialdini关于毛巾实验的研究问题。</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>定位关键词: &quot;towel experiment,&quot; &quot;research question&quot;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>对应原文: C段,“Cialdini and his colleagues wanted to test the relative effectiveness of different text on those cards.”</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>解题思路: <span style=\"text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">C段</span>提到<span style=\"text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">Cialdini 和同事</span>实验的目的是测试酒店卡片上的不同信息对客人的行为的不同影响。</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            </div><div class=\"big-section\">\r\n            <div class=\"q-block normal-q\">\r\n                <div class=\"q-stem\">\r\n                    <span class=\"q-num\">31</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"q-text\"><p><strong>The results of the towel experiment suggest that guests</strong></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"opt-list\" style=\"margin:10px 0 10px 25px;\">\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_31\" id=\"opt_31_A\" data-zyz-question=\"q31\" value=\"A\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_31_A\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>A.</strong> were disinclined to tell the truth about towel use.</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_31\" id=\"opt_31_B\" data-zyz-question=\"q31\" value=\"B\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_31_B\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>B.</strong> preferred not to receive a message with their towels</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_31\" id=\"opt_31_C\" data-zyz-question=\"q31\" value=\"C\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_31_C\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>C.</strong> were more receptive to messages about other guests</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_31\" id=\"opt_31_D\" data-zyz-question=\"q31\" value=\"D\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_31_D\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>D.</strong> responded more positively to an environmental message.</label>\r\n        </div></div>\r\n                <button class=\"btn-toggle\">显示解析</button>\r\n                <div class=\"ans-box\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-row\"><strong>正确答案：</strong> C. were more receptive to messages about other guests</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"analysis\"><p>审题: 题目问的是毛巾实验的结果显示客人有什么反应。</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>定位关键词: &quot;towel experiment,&quot; &quot;results&quot;,&quot;guests&quot;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>对应原文: D段,“To test this, the researchers redesigned the cards, replacing the environmental message with the simple (and truthful) statement that the majority of guests at the hotel had reused their towel at least once.&nbsp;Those guests who received this message were found to be 26% more likely to reuse their towel than those given the original message, and 74% more likely than those receiving no message at all.”</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>解题思路: <span style=\"text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">&nbsp;D段</span>提到结果显示，当客人知道其他人也重复使用毛巾时，他们更可能效仿。</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            </div><div class=\"big-section\"><div class=\"group-instruction\"><p><strong>Questions 32 - 36</strong></p><p><br/></p><p>Complete the summary using the list of words. Choose the correct word and move it into the gap.</p></div>\r\n    <div class=\"word-bank-container\">\r\n        <div class=\"wb-title\">Options (Word Bank):</div>\r\n        <div class=\"wb-grid\">\r\n            <div class=\"wb-item\"><strong>A.</strong> rare opportunity</div><div class=\"wb-item\"><strong>B.</strong> previous commitments</div><div class=\"wb-item\"><strong>C.</strong> generous response</div><div class=\"wb-item\"><strong>D.</strong> true qualification</div><div class=\"wb-item\"><strong>E.</strong> similar name</div><div class=\"wb-item\"><strong>F.</strong> ruthless exploitation</div><div class=\"wb-item\"><strong>G.</strong> social obligation</div><div class=\"wb-item\"><strong>H.</strong> relative value</div><div class=\"wb-item\"><strong>I.</strong> bad behavior</div><div class=\"wb-item\"><strong>J.</strong> small favor</div>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n                    <div class=\"q-block normal-q\">\r\n                        <div class=\"q-stem\">\r\n                            <span class=\"q-num\">32</span>\r\n                            <div class=\"q-text\"><p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"></span></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>The six principles of persuasion</strong></p><p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><br/></span></p><p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Cialdini’s towel experiment demonstrated the principle he named ‘social proof’, which can result in competitive materialism. His research using chocolates suggests that people don’t always assess the <span class=\"input-blank\" data-question=\"q32\"></span> of transaction.</span><br/></p></div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <button class=\"btn-toggle\">显示解析</button>\r\n                        <div class=\"ans-box\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n                            <div class=\"ans-row\"><strong>正确答案：</strong> H</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"analysis\"><p>审题：题目问的是Cialdini实验中人们在交易时评估的特定内容。</p><p><br/></p><p>定位关键词: assess, the relative value of transaction</p><p><br/></p><p>对应原文：E段，A further principle, which he names ‘reciprocity’, was tested in a restaurant by measuring how patrons would respond to after-dinner chocolates.</p><p><br/></p><p><span style=\"text-wrap-mode: wrap;\"><span style=\"text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">解题思路:&nbsp;</span>E段</span>提到<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Cialdini的</span>研究表明人们往往不能准确地评估交易的相对价值。</p><p><br/></p><p>同义替换：&nbsp;research=tested</p></div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    \r\n                    <div class=\"q-block normal-q\">\r\n                        <div class=\"q-stem\">\r\n                            <span class=\"q-num\">33</span>\r\n                            <div class=\"q-text\"><p>A further principle recommends that advertisers and parents should claim that something is a <span class=\"input-blank\" data-question=\"q33\"></span> .</p></div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <button class=\"btn-toggle\">显示解析</button>\r\n                        <div class=\"ans-box\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n                            <div class=\"ans-row\"><strong>正确答案：</strong> A</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"analysis\"><p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"></span>审题：题目问的是广告商和家长推荐的特定事物的描述。</p><p><br/></p><p>定位关键词:&nbsp;advertisers and parents</p><p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><br/></span></p><p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">对应原文：F段，‘Scarcity’ is the idea that people want more of things they can have less of, a notion that ‘advertisers ruthlessly exploit-limit of four per customer’. Parents can also make use of scarcity by telling their little ones that this is a very unusual chance so they should seize it immediately.&nbsp;</span></p><p><br/></p><p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">解题思路:&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">F段</span>提到“稀缺性”原则，人们更想要稀缺的东西，广告商会利用这一点宣传“限时优惠”等信息。</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><br/></span></p><p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">同义替换：rare opportunity = scarcity</span></p></div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    \r\n                    <div class=\"q-block normal-q\">\r\n                        <div class=\"q-stem\">\r\n                            <span class=\"q-num\">34</span>\r\n                            <div class=\"q-text\"><p>In order to be more persuasive, the authority principle is often ignored when some professionals are concerned their actions might be considered <span class=\"input-blank\" data-question=\"q34\"></span>.&nbsp;</p></div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <button class=\"btn-toggle\">显示解析</button>\r\n                        <div class=\"ans-box\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n                            <div class=\"ans-row\"><strong>正确答案：</strong> I</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"analysis\"><p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"></span></p><p>审题：题目问的是某些专业人士在考虑行为被视为某种特定特点下忽视权威原则。</p><p><br/></p><p style=\"text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">定位关键词:&nbsp;<span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\">the authority principle, professionals</span></p><p style=\"text-wrap-mode: wrap;\"><br/></p><p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">对应原文：F段，The principle of ‘authority’ states that we trust people who know what they are talking about. Cialdini maintains that many professionals don&#39;t display their credentials, fearing it is boastful or arrogant to publicise their expertise.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br/></p><p><br/></p><p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">解题思路：<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">F段</span>提到“权威”原则强调信任专业人士，但一些专业人士担心展示资历会被看作自负或傲慢。</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><br/></span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:arial, helvetica, sans-serif\">同义替换：</span>bad behavior = boastful or arrogant</p></div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    \r\n                    <div class=\"q-block normal-q\">\r\n                        <div class=\"q-stem\">\r\n                            <span class=\"q-num\">35</span>\r\n                            <div class=\"q-text\"><p>He similarly suggests that people will give more to charity if they can be reminded of <span class=\"input-blank\" data-question=\"q35\"></span>.</p></div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <button class=\"btn-toggle\">显示解析</button>\r\n                        <div class=\"ans-box\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n                            <div class=\"ans-row\"><strong>正确答案：</strong> B</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"analysis\"><p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"></span></p><p>审题：题目问的是人们在被提醒什么特定内容时会更愿意捐赠。</p><p><br/></p><p>定位关键词:&nbsp;give more to charity</p><p><br/></p><p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">对应原文：F段, ”The principle he labels ‘consistency’ </span>suggests that we want to act in ways that are consistent with undertaking we have already made.”</p><p><br/></p><p>解题思路：F段提到“一致性”原则，人们倾向于与之前做出的承诺保持一致。</p><p><br/></p><p>同义替换：previous=already made</p><p>commitments= undertakings&nbsp;</p></div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    \r\n                    <div class=\"q-block normal-q\">\r\n                        <div class=\"q-stem\">\r\n                            <span class=\"q-num\">36</span>\r\n                            <div class=\"q-text\"><p>Lastly, even something like a <span class=\"input-blank\" data-question=\"q36\"></span> has been shown to result in more surveys being completed.&nbsp;</p></div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <button class=\"btn-toggle\">显示解析</button>\r\n                        <div class=\"ans-box\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n                            <div class=\"ans-row\"><strong>正确答案：</strong> E</div>\r\n                            <div class=\"analysis\"><p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"text-wrap-mode: wrap;\"></span></span></p><p style=\"text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">审题：<span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\">题目问的是什么事物能够促进更多调查被完成的效果。</span></p><p><br/></p><p>定位关键词:&nbsp;surveys, completed</p><p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"text-wrap-mode: wrap;\"><br/></span></span></p><p>对应原文：F段,The final principle is ‘likeness’：we are more easily persuaded by those who seem similar to ourselves. In one study, people were sent survey forms and asked to return them to a named researcher. When the researcher falsely identified herself (e.g. Cynthia Johnson is sent a survey by ‘Cindy Johansen’), surveys were twice as likely to be completed.</p><p><br/></p><p>解题思路：F段提到“相似性”原则，人们更容易被与自己相似的人说服。研究发现，当调查问卷署名与被调查者姓名相似时，完成问卷的比例会增加一倍。</p></div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    </div><div class=\"big-section\"><div class=\"group-instruction\"><p><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\"><strong>Questions 37 - 40</strong></span></p><p><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\"><br/></span></p><p><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\">Choose </span><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\"><strong>YES</strong></span><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\"> if the statement agrees with the claims of the writer, choose</span><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\"><strong> NO </strong></span><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\">if the statement contradicts the claims of the writer, or choose </span><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\"><strong>NOT GIVEN</strong></span><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\"> if it is impossible to say what the writer thinks about this.</span></p></div>\r\n            <div class=\"q-block normal-q\">\r\n                <div class=\"q-stem\">\r\n                    <span class=\"q-num\">37</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"q-text\"><p><strong>The writer sees evidence of the reciprocity principle in his own family.</strong></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"opt-list\" style=\"margin:10px 0 10px 25px;\">\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_37\" id=\"opt_37_A\" data-zyz-question=\"q37\" value=\"A\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_37_A\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>A.</strong> YES</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_37\" id=\"opt_37_B\" data-zyz-question=\"q37\" value=\"B\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_37_B\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>B.</strong> NO</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_37\" id=\"opt_37_C\" data-zyz-question=\"q37\" value=\"C\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_37_C\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>C.</strong> NOT GIVEN</label>\r\n        </div></div>\r\n                <button class=\"btn-toggle\">显示解析</button>\r\n                <div class=\"ans-box\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-row\"><strong>正确答案：</strong> C. NOT GIVEN</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"analysis\"><p>审题: 题目问作者是否在自己的家庭中看到了互惠原则的证据。</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>定位关键词: “reciprocity principle,” “own family”</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>对应原文: G段, ”Many of Cialdini’s claims about persuasion are just that – highly persuasive – and I can readily see evidence for some of them in my own workplace.&nbsp;”</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>解题思路: <span style=\"text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">G段提到</span>作者在自己的工作中遇到了许多Cialdini对于说服的说法，但没有提到作者在自己的家庭中是否看到过互惠原则的证据。</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            </div><div class=\"big-section\">\r\n            <div class=\"q-block normal-q\">\r\n                <div class=\"q-stem\">\r\n                    <span class=\"q-num\">38</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"q-text\"><p><strong>Persuasion may operate in different ways in different countries.</strong></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"opt-list\" style=\"margin:10px 0 10px 25px;\">\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_38\" id=\"opt_38_A\" data-zyz-question=\"q38\" value=\"A\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_38_A\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>A.</strong> YES</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_38\" id=\"opt_38_B\" data-zyz-question=\"q38\" value=\"B\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_38_B\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>B.</strong> NO</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_38\" id=\"opt_38_C\" data-zyz-question=\"q38\" value=\"C\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_38_C\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>C.</strong> NOT GIVEN</label>\r\n        </div></div>\r\n                <button class=\"btn-toggle\">显示解析</button>\r\n                <div class=\"ans-box\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-row\"><strong>正确答案：</strong> A. YES</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"analysis\"><p>审题: 题目问作者是否认为不同国家的说服方式不同。</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>定位关键词: “persuasion,” “different countries”</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>对应原文: G段，&quot;But Cialdini’s experiments were conducted in the United States and I wonder how well all of his findings can be applied here in New Zealand or elsewhere around the world.&quot;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>解题思路: G段提到Cialdini的实验是在美国进行的，作者怀疑他的所有发现能否同样适用于新西兰或世界其他地方。这表明作者认为不同国家的文化背景可能会导致劝说方法在不同国家产生不同的效果。</p><p><br/></p><p>同义替换：&nbsp;operate=be applied；different countries=around the world.</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            </div><div class=\"big-section\">\r\n            <div class=\"q-block normal-q\">\r\n                <div class=\"q-stem\">\r\n                    <span class=\"q-num\">39</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"q-text\"><p><strong>New Zealand diners are likely to leave tips if they are given chocolate.</strong></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"opt-list\" style=\"margin:10px 0 10px 25px;\">\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_39\" id=\"opt_39_A\" data-zyz-question=\"q39\" value=\"A\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_39_A\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>A.</strong> YES</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_39\" id=\"opt_39_B\" data-zyz-question=\"q39\" value=\"B\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_39_B\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>B.</strong> NO</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_39\" id=\"opt_39_C\" data-zyz-question=\"q39\" value=\"C\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_39_C\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>C.</strong> NOT GIVEN</label>\r\n        </div></div>\r\n                <button class=\"btn-toggle\">显示解析</button>\r\n                <div class=\"ans-box\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-row\"><strong>正确答案：</strong> B. NO</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"analysis\"><p>审题: 题目问新西兰的食客是否会因收到巧克力而留下小费。</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>定位关键词: “New Zealand,” “tips,” “chocolate”</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>对应原文: G段，&quot;&nbsp;For instance, I do understand the general principle of ‘reciprocity’ but cannot imagine New Zealand waiting staff using his cynical chocolate trick in their restaurants because the culture of tipping in this country is so different.&nbsp;&quot;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>解题思路: G段提到，作者认为新西兰的小费文化与美国等其他国家不同，并且巧克力的小费技巧在新西兰并不适用。这意味着，即使给新西兰食客巧克力，他们也不太可能因此而给小费。</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            </div><div class=\"big-section\">\r\n            <div class=\"q-block normal-q\">\r\n                <div class=\"q-stem\">\r\n                    <span class=\"q-num\">40</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"q-text\"><p><strong>Older New Zealanders would be more attracted to consistency.</strong></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"opt-list\" style=\"margin:10px 0 10px 25px;\">\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_40\" id=\"opt_40_A\" data-zyz-question=\"q40\" value=\"A\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_40_A\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>A.</strong> YES</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_40\" id=\"opt_40_B\" data-zyz-question=\"q40\" value=\"B\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_40_B\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>B.</strong> NO</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_40\" id=\"opt_40_C\" data-zyz-question=\"q40\" value=\"C\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_40_C\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>C.</strong> NOT GIVEN</label>\r\n        </div></div>\r\n                <button class=\"btn-toggle\">显示解析</button>\r\n                <div class=\"ans-box\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-row\"><strong>正确答案：</strong> B. NO</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"analysis\"><p>审题: 题目问的是年长的新西兰人是否更倾向于一致性原则。</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>定位关键词: “older New Zealanders,” “consistency”</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>对应原文: G段，&quot;It may be that age is also a factor and that different generations would react differently to say, the ‘consistency’ principle. I suspect that younger people in this country would respond quite positively to this sort of approach, whereas their parents might be put off by any hint of a hard sell.&quot;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>解题思路: <span style=\"text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">G段</span>提到不同年龄段的人对“<span style=\"text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">consistency&nbsp;<span style=\"text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">principle</span></span>”的反应不同。作者认为年轻人更愿意接受这种方式，而年长者则不接受这种强行推销的方式。</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            </div>",
